records.addlTxt:
The State files a Second Amended Information which charges two counts possess controlled substance, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(d) and one count possess drug paraphernalia, contrary to Section 961.573(1).
GUILTY pleas entered to counts 1 and 2 of the Second Amended Information. Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
5) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) complete fifty (50) hours community service within the first six months, on count 1only.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of probation with no positive UAs, no new criminal offenses and no new ordinance offenses that are drug related or alcohol related.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter. 
Letter from Kettle Moraine Counseling Services.
Minutes.
